        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34239",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is expected behavior. 'edit' is a special target, as the code implies. To go to the editAction for a resource, you use the following URI:\n\n\/page\/1\/edit\n\nShould route to PageController::editAction() with am 'id' param of 1.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-04T06:45:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-04T06:45:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34240",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admloki",
                        "name": "admloki",
                        "displayName": "Alex Zinchenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No, it's not.\n\nKey to value mapping appears before 'edit' target check:\n{code}\n\/\/ Digest URI params\nif ($numSegs = count($path)) {\n    for ($i = 0; $i < $numSegs; $i = $i + 2) {\n        $key = urldecode($path[$i]);\n        $val = isset($path[$i + 1]) ? urldecode($path[$i + 1]) : null;\n        $params[$key] = $val;\n    }\n}\n\n\/\/ Check for trailing \"special get\" URI\nif (array_key_exists('edit', $params)) {\n    $specialGetTarget = 'edit';\n}\n{code}\n\nBut 'edit' appears not as an array key, but value:\n{code}\n\/\/match() result dump\narray(3) { [\"controller\"]=>  string(4) \"page\" [\"action\"]=>  string(5) \"index\" [1]=>  string(4) \"edit\" } \n{code}\n\nBut even change 'array_key_exists' to 'in_array' it willn't help for other actions.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admloki",
                        "name": "admloki",
                        "displayName": "Alex Zinchenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-04T07:02:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-04T07:02:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34255",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If you want to invoke PageController::editAction($id = 1) you use this URI:\n\n\/page\/1\/edit\n\nThe paradigm for GET requests in the route is:\n\n\/{resource}\/new\nor\n\/{resource}\/{identifier}\nor\n\/{resource}\/{identifier}\/edit\nor\n\/{resource}\/index\/{param_name}\/{param_value}\/{param_name}\/{param_value}\n\nTo enable something like '\/page\/edit\/1' as PageController::editAction is to break with the intended paradigm of the route.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-04T13:57:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-04T13:57:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34258",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admloki",
                        "name": "admloki",
                        "displayName": "Alex Zinchenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sometimes i get feeling nobody read what i wrote.\nZend_Rest_Route will not map route like \/page\/1\/edit. \n\nIt will map \/page\/edit\/, but with wrong values: \n{code}\narray(3) { [\"controller\"]=>  string(4) \"page\" [\"action\"]=>  string(4) \"edit\" [\"edit\"]=>  string(1) \"1\" } \n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=admloki",
                        "name": "admloki",
                        "displayName": "Alex Zinchenko",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-05T04:14:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-05T04:14:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34276",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ah, I see now. I think I lost what the issue was in all the code and commentary of the first comment. I have a test to reproduce, but I'm using a different fix that will preserve the index functionality, the textual identifiers, and not confuse the order of the action value and id values.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-06T18:57:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-06T18:57:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34278",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Should now be fixed so a URI like:\n\n\/page\/1\/edit\n\nreturns with from match with controller => page; id => 1; action => edit",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lcrouch",
                        "name": "lcrouch",
                        "displayName": "Luke Crouch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-06T19:03:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-06T19:03:58.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
